content.description:
from rockclimbing.com - "Start at the base of an imposing chimney between a skyscaper sized detached tower and the main wall. shimmy up some easy 5th class (5.4?, 60ft, 2 bolts) to the belay/rapstation on top of a huge chock stone in the chimney. Proceed directly up the chimney, past the chockstone to a bolted anchor with chains. (5.7+/5.8, 90ft, 6 bolts) Two raps to the ground with a single 60M, or a single double rope rap on the outside of the spire."
from the last belay station you can trad up the last short easy pitch to the top of the spire, but you'll have to down climb back to said belay station.

bolted

(from rockclimbing.com) "A huge (280ft) diorite cliff on the shore of Cummings Lk, this Cliff has had spotty development (mainly due to the rock quality and poison ivy). The quality of the routes that have been developed are steller, with a mix of crack and bolted face climbing. (and great potential for far more lines) Crags just waiting for development abound - check with the locals for information."
